        <h3 class="article__heading">01. Challenge</h3>

        <p>Groups Recover Together is an organization that helps its 6,000+ members recover from opioid addiction in 80+ physical locations across the United States. They do this by coupling weekly group therapy sessions with prescriptions to Suboxone (a treatment that reduces withdrawal symptoms). They also have members create and uphold Treatment Plans, which keeps them motivated and accountable on their path to recovery.</p>

        <p>They approached us in the fall of 2020, eight months after they had to close their physical locations due to the COVID-19 pandemic. In the time leading up to working with us, they quickly scrapped together a solution that would move their staff operations and group therapy sessions online. They were worried about the switch to remote therapy via video conferencing, for they were unsure of its efficacy and ability to retain and find new members. However, much to their surprise and delight, they discovered that virtual care not only yields similar clinical outcomes to in-person care, but can improve access and retention.</p>

