        <p>This brings us to the work we did together. Armed with the positive data they needed to measure the efficacy of virtual treatment, they decided to hire a product design and development partner to create a scalable, seamless, and polished online platform ‚Äì not only for new and existing members, but for their staff as well.</p>


        <h3 class="article__heading">02. Process</h3>

        <h2 class="article__subheader">Empathize</h2>
        <p>I led our team of three developers, two designers (myself included), and six Groups teammates through a Product Design Sprint to uncover our assumptions, identify user pain points, brainstorm ideas, and align on a path forward. There were many possibilities for what the first version of this new platform will include, so we gathered to answer two questions in order to begin design and development:</p>

