        <h2 class="article__subheader" id="treatmentplan">Updating the Treatment Plan</h2>

        <p>The Treatment Plan is something that every member has to create and maintain throughout their time at Groups ‚Äì and until now was always done in person, on paper. It holds them accountable to enact positive change in their lives. It comprises of at least three goals, each broken down into smaller achievable objectives ‚Äì and each one of those objectives has modularities. It can get real complicated real quick, and the design and build of the Treatment Plan was a whole project in and of itself. There were lots of decisions to make: How do we help members make batch updates? How do they copy over unresolved objectives to the next plan? How do they create new goals? Designing it was truly an iterative process, and was informed by user testing sessions to get it to where it is today.</p>


