        <h2 class="article__subheader">Onboarding Content</h2>

        <p>We also talked about how and when to show members articles, videos, and other pieces of important content. The Groups team has a bunch of informative, well-produced, well-thought out content that's important for a member to view ‚Äì to not only help them onboard but to help them feel less alone in their journey. Due to the importance of this content, I knew that context, quantity, and relevance were key to getting members to engage with particular articles or videos.</p>

        <p>Therefore, rather than putting all the content in a separate section of the app, I recommended that we instead only serve up a couple pieces of content at a time on the home screen, that depend on where a member is in their journey. For example, a new member who has yet to go through the intake process will see different articles from someone who has completed their first group therapy session.</p>


